    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-10-21T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-10-21T11:00:00-05:00" n="701"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d701">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">683.84A322/10–2153: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 701<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Syria (<persName corresp="#p_MJS1"
                            type="from">Moose</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d701fn1">A copy of this telegram was sent by Secretary
                            <persName corresp="#p_DJF2">Dulles</persName> to President <persName
                            corresp="#p_EGAD1">Eisenhower</persName> on Oct. 23 under cover of a
                        memorandum which reads: “You may be interested in the attached cable from
                        Syria.” (683.84A322/10–2153)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Damascus</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-10-21T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 21, 1953—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>156. Pursuant instructions <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 143, October
                    19 I saw <persName corresp="#p_ASGA1">Shishakli</persName> at noon today. He at
                    once expressed gratification over Secretary’s statement to press concerning
                    deferment further US aid Israel, noting that US action was promoted by Israel
                    flouting <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> authority re diversion Jordan River
                    in demilitarized zone. He said action had increased his confidence in US
                    administration and in President <persName corresp="#p_EGAD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName> and gave him hope for the future.</p>
                <p>I conveyed contents reference telegram and expressed firm desire for peaceful
                    settlement. He observed, however, that Israel continues to work on the diversion
                    canal in defiance <gloss target="#t_UNTSO1">UNTSO</gloss> and said if peaceful
                    means fail Syrian Government could not divest itself of responsibility to
                    protect legitimate Syrian interests. While admitting Israel could not completely
                    divert Jordan for some time to come, he asserted that Arab-owned mill and farm
                    called Aalmine had already been deprived of water.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Comment:</hi> I have never before seen <persName
                        corresp="#p_ASGA1">Shishakli</persName> so well disposed toward US. I feel
                    confident he will continue exercise restraining influence while awaiting outcome
                    present <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
